WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.126
Every cell is a tiny chemical factory. Feed it sugar, and

2
00:00:03.226 --> 00:00:06.012
it has to decide where all that carbon should flow.

3
00:00:06.900 --> 00:00:09.384
Think of its metabolism as a network of pipes.

4
00:00:09.484 --> 00:00:12.531
Sugar enters here, and splits between building new cells

5
00:00:12.631 --> 00:00:14.610
and making the product we care about.

6
00:00:14.700 --> 00:00:17.946
The key rule is balance. At steady state nothing is allowed to

7
00:00:18.046 --> 00:00:21.130
pile up: whatever flows into a junction must flow back out.

8
00:00:22.200 --> 00:00:25.228
So the cell is really solving a routing puzzle: given a

9
00:00:25.328 --> 00:00:28.186
fixed sugar supply, which split of the flow is best?

10
00:00:28.266 --> 00:00:32.087
Flux Balance Analysis picks the routing that maximises our objective —

11
00:00:32.187 --> 00:00:35.167
here, the precursor that feeds the rest of the toolkit.

12
00:00:38.066 --> 00:00:40.311
No new chemistry is invented — it is simply

13
00:00:40.411 --> 00:00:42.819
the best traffic plan on a fixed road network.

14
00:00:42.919 --> 00:00:46.090
That single number sets the stage for everything downstream.

